ul, I., Zhao, G., Properties of novel fluorinated compounds and their mixtures as alternative refrigerants (1998) Fluid Phase Equilib., 150-151, pp. 287-296; Hou, H., Holste, J.C., Gammon, B.E., Marsh, K.N., Experimental densities for compressed R134a (1992) Int. J. Refrig., 15, pp. 365-371; Kayukawa, Y., Hasumoto, M., Hondo, T., Kano, Y., Watanabe, K., Thermodynamic property measurements for trifluoromethyl methyl ether and pentafluoroethyl methyl ether (2003) J. Chem. Eng. Data, 48, pp. 1141-1151; Kilicarslan, A., Muller, N., A comparative study of water as a refrigerant with somecurrent refrigerants (2005) Int. J. Energy Res., 29, pp. 947-959","Blowers, P.; Department of Chemical and Environmental Engineering, University of Arizona, Tucson, AZ 85721-0011, United States; email: blowers@email.arizona.edu",,,,,,,,0013936X,,ESTHA,20050659,"English","Environ. Sci. Technol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-77749264884
